heverge.com/netflix)\n    -   [YouTube](https://www.theverge.com/youtube)\n    -   [Creators](https://www.theverge.com/creators)\n    -   [See all streaming](https://www.theverge.com/streaming)\n    \n-   TransportationExpand\n    \n    -   [Electric Cars](https://www.theverge.com/electric-cars)\n    -   [Autonomous Cars](https://www.theverge.com/autonomous-cars)\n    -   [Ride-sharing](https://www.theverge.com/ride-sharing)\n    -   [Scooters](https://www.theverge.com/scooters)\n    -   [See all transportation](/transportation)\n    \n-   [Features](https://www.theverge.com/features)\n-   Verge VideoExpand\n    \n    -   [TikTok](https://www.tiktok.com/@verge)\n    -   [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/theverge)\n    -   [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/verge)\n    \n-   PodcastsExpand\n    \n    -   [Decoder](/decoder-podcast-with-nilay-patel)\n    -   [The Vergecast](/the-vergecast)\n    -   [Version History](/version-history-podcast)\n    \n-   [Newsletters](/newsletters)\n-   [Archives](/archives/full)\n-   [Store](https://shop.theverge.com/)\n-   [Verge Product Updates](https://www.theverge.com/verge-product-updates)\n\n[Subscribe](/subscribe?itm_campaign=menu-nav-subscribe&itm_medium=site&itm_source=navigation)\n\n-   [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/verge)\n-   [Threads](https://www.threads.net/@verge)\n-   [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/verge)\n-   [Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/user/theverge)\n-   [RSS](https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml)\n\n# AI\n\nFollowFollow\n\nArtificial intelligence is more a part of our lives than ever before. While some might call it hype and compare it to NFTs or 3D TVs, generative AI is causing a sea change in nearly every part of the technology industry. OpenAI’s ChatGPT is still the best-known AI chatbot around, but with Google pushing Gemini, Microsoft building Copilot, and Apple adding its Intelligence to Siri, AI is probably going to be in the spotlight for a very long time. At The Verge, we’re exploring what might be possible with AI — and a lot of the bad stuff AI does, too.\n\n-   RELATED /\n-   Anthropic\n    \n    Close\n    \n    Anthropic\n    \n    Posts from this topic will be added to your daily email digest and your homepage feed.\n    \n    FollowFollow\n    \n    [See All Anthropic](/anthropic)\n    \n-   xAI\n    \n    Close\n    \n    xAI\n    \n    Posts from this topic will be added to your daily email digest and your homepage feed.\n    \n    FollowFollow\n    \n    [See All xAI](/x-ai)\n    \n\n![Lorde says Ray-Ban Meta AI glasses are ‘not sexy’](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/gettyimages-2279420244.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0.094572966681213%2C100%2C99.810854066638&w=2400)\n\n[Lorde says Ray-Ban Meta AI glasses are ‘not sexy’](/ai-artificial-intelligence/964539/lorde-says-ray-ban-meta-ai-glasses-are-not-sexy)\n\n‘Fuck the glasses.’\n\nTerrence O'BrienJul 12\n\n![Apple’s failed self-driving car program left a legacy of powerful AI chips](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/03/apple_chips.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0.0099980003999178%2C100%2C99.9800039992&w=2400)\n\n[Apple’s failed self-driving car program left a legacy of powerful AI chips](/tech/964519/apple-silicon-self-driving-car-ai-m7-ultra)\n\nThe company is accelerating development of the M7 Ultra, which could support up to 1.5TB of RAM.\n\nTerrence O'BrienJul 12\n\n## Latest In AI\n\n![The fight against AI data centers is just beginning](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/gettyimages-2282688394.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0.0050000000000026%2C0%2C99.99%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[The fight against AI data centers is just beginning](/column/963346/ai-data-centers-fight)\n\nCommunity pushback from across the US and beyond is making some companies reconsider their data center buildout plans.\n\nEmma RothJul 12\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/964489/openais-head-of-safety-is-out)\n\n![Terrence O'Brien](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/TERRENCE_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nTerrence O'BrienJul 11\n\nOpenAI’s head of safety is out.\n\nTurnovers at that ChatGPT maker continue. The company’s chief futurist, [Joshua Achiam](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962540/openais-chief-futurist-is-leaving-the-company-after-nine-years), and AGI head, [Fidji Simo](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963738/openai-fidji-simo-steps-down-ceo-advisor), announced their departures earlier this week. Now [Johannes Heidecke](https://www.wired.com/story/openai-head-of-safety-leaving/), who has overseen OpenAI’s safety efforts, is out, as [ChatGPT 5.6](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963464/openai-gpt-5-6-codex-chatgpt-work) rolls out and [raises some alarms](/ai-artificial-intelligence/957845/openai-gpt-5-6-trump-administration-ai-preview).\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/964433/openais-greg-brockman-will-keep-heading-up-product-at-the-company)\n\n![Jay Peters](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/JAY_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nJay PetersJul 11\n\nOpenAI’s Greg Brockman will keep heading up product at the company.\n\nBrockman had taken over product when Fidji Simo went on [medical leave](/ai-artificial-intelligence/906965/openais-agi-boss-is-taking-a-leave-of-absence), and he’ll continue those responsibilities now that Simo is [stepping down](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963738/openai-fidji-simo-steps-down-ceo-advisor) from her full-time OpenAI job and becoming a “part-time advisor,” [CNBC reports](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/07/10/openai-power-consolidates-under-co-founder-greg-brockman-ahead-of-ipo.html).\n\n[OpenAI power consolidates under co-founder Greg Brockman ahead of prospective IPO](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/07/10/openai-power-consolidates-under-co-founder-greg-brockman-ahead-of-ipo.html)\n\n\\[CNBC\\]\n\nLink\n\n![Meta turns off the Instagram feature that let users make AI deepfakes of public accounts](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/meta-muse-image-instagram-tag.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=11.111111111111%2C0%2C77.777777777778%2C100&w=2400)![Meta turns off the Instagram feature that let users make AI deepfakes of public accounts](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/meta-muse-image-instagram-tag.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C7.1428571428571%2C100%2C85.714285714286&w=2400)\n\n[Meta turns off the Instagram feature that let users make AI deepfakes of public accounts](/tech/964416/meta-instagram-ai-muse-image-deepfakes)\n\nJay PetersJul 10\n\n![Apple sues OpenAI for allegedly stealing hardware secrets](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/04/STK468_APPLE_ANTITRUST_CVIRGINIA_D.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.666666666667%2C0%2C66.666666666667%2C100&w=2400)![Apple sues OpenAI for allegedly stealing hardware secrets](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/04/STK468_APPLE_ANTITRUST_CVIRGINIA_D.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Apple sues OpenAI for allegedly stealing hardware secrets](/tech/964350/apple-openai-lawsuit-trade-secrets)\n\nJay PetersJul 10\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/964293/openais-standalone-codex-app-is-here-to-stay)\n\n![Emma Roth](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/195810/EMMA_ROTH.0.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nEmma RothJul 10\n\nOpenAI’s standalone Codex app is “here to stay.”\n\nThibault Sottiaux, the engineering lead on Codex, [clarified on X](https://x.com/thsottiaux/status/2075641131002700120) that the company isn’t sunsetting its AI coding tool [despite the launch of ChatGPT Work](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963464/openai-gpt-5-6-codex-chatgpt-work), a platform that combines both ChatGPT and Codex. Sottiaux teased some other updates coming to the Work app as well, like moving chats and projects into the sidebar.\n\n[ChatGPT Work update](https://x.com/thsottiaux/status/2075641131002700120)\n\n\\[@thsottiaux on X (formerly Twitter)\\]\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/964020/putting-the-ai-in-airport)\n\n![Emma Roth](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/195810/EMMA_ROTH.0.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nEmma RothJul 10\n\nPutting the “AI” in airport.\n\nThis [report from *Futurism*](https://futurism.com/artificial-intelligence/trump-airport-logo-ai) dives into some of the inconsistencies in the logo for the [newly-renamed](https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/us/politics/donald-trump-palm-beach-airport.html) President Donald J. Trump International Airport. The shield only [has 11 stripes](/gadgets/931347/trump-mobile-t1-phone-logo-flag-stars-stripes), instead of 13; the eagle’s right-side talons look distorted; and there’s an uneven number of feathers and leaves.\n\n[![](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/trump-airport-logo.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.9119313300739%2C0%2C92.088068669926%2C100&w=2400)](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/trump-airport-logo.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.9119313300739,0,92.088068669926,100)\n\nImage: President Donald J. Trump International Airport\n\nLink\n\n![Instagram’s Adam Mosseri: If you don’t like AI, ‘then you shouldn’t have it in your feed’](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/gettyimages-2239561028.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.75%2C0%2C66.5%2C100&w=2400)![Instagram’s Adam Mosseri: If you don’t like AI, ‘then you shouldn’t have it in your feed’](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/gettyimages-2239561028.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0.125%2C0%2C99.75%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Instagram’s Adam Mosseri: If you don’t like AI, ‘then you shouldn’t have it in your feed’](/tech/963961/instagram-adam-mosseri-ai-feed-filters)\n\nEmma RothJul 10\n\n![Would you host part of an AI data center in your home?](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/sunrun-distributed-compute1.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=43.333333333333%2C0%2C56.666666666667%2C100&w=2400)![Would you host part of an AI data center in your home?](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/sunrun-distributed-compute1.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=15%2C0%2C85%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Would you host part of an AI data center in your home?](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963930/sunrun-distributed-ai-data-center)\n\nStevie BonifieldJul 10\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963866/the-randian-response)\n\n![Dominic Preston](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/DOM_BLURPLE-1.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nDominic PrestonJul 10\n\nThe Randian response.\n\nOpenAI is [shutting down](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963654/openai-chatgpt-atlas-ai-browser-shut-down-sunset#comments) its ChatGPT web browser, and there’s only one appropriate reaction.\n\n**better-endings:**\n\n> Atlas? *shrug*\n\nGet the day’s best comment and more in my free newsletter, [*The Verge Daily*](/newsletters).\n\nLink\n\n[](/tech/963626/tiktok-aims-to-catch-more-accounts-posting-ai-spam)\n\n![Emma Roth](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/195810/EMMA_ROTH.0.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nEmma RothJul 10\n\nTikTok aims to catch more accounts posting AI spam.\n\nThe platform is testing improvements to its spam detection system to help identify accounts posting AI-generated spam related to politics, current events, financial advice, medical information, and other topics that could “pose a risk to public trust or well-being.”\n\nTikTok is also joining the [C2PA Steering Committee](/ai-artificial-intelligence/934521/google-synthid-c2pa-content-credentials-ai-labelling-efforts).\n\nLink\n\n![Microsoft’s carbon emissions went up 25 percent last year](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/04/STKS528_DATA_CENTERS_A.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.666666666667%2C0%2C66.666666666667%2C100&w=2400)![Microsoft’s carbon emissions went up 25 percent last year](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/04/STKS528_DATA_CENTERS_A.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Microsoft’s carbon emissions went up 25 percent last year](/tech/963728/microsoft-sustainability-report-2026)\n\nStevie BonifieldJul 10\n\n![Fidji Simo steps down from leading OpenAI’s AGI work due to illness](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/gettyimages-1239232101.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.675%2C0%2C66.65%2C100&w=2400)![Fidji Simo steps down from leading OpenAI’s AGI work due to illness](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/gettyimages-1239232101.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0.012500000000003%2C0%2C99.975%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Fidji Simo steps down from leading OpenAI’s AGI work due to illness](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963738/openai-fidji-simo-steps-down-ceo-advisor)\n\nHayden Field and Jay PetersJul 9\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963723/patreon-is-working-with-cloudflare-to-squash-ai-crawlers)\n\n![Emma Roth](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/195810/EMMA_ROTH.0.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nEmma RothJul 9\n\nPatreon is working with Cloudflare to squash AI crawlers.\n\nIn [a post on Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/p/Dak02PFPnEL/?ref=404media.co), Patreon CEO Jack Conte says the move will prevent AI crawlers from training on creators’ work. Last year, [Cloudflare began blocking](/news/695501/cloudflare-block-ai-crawlers-default) AI crawlers by default and [recently announced](/ai-artificial-intelligence/960795/cloudflare-is-cracking-down-on-multi-purpose-crawlers) plans to give publishers more granular control of the kinds of scrapers they allow in.\n\n[Patreon Blocks Crawlers From Stealing Creators' Work for AI Training](https://www.404media.co/patreon-cloudflare-partnership-ai-crawlers/)\n\n\\[404 Media\\]\n\nLink\n\n![The ChatGPT browser is already dead](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/10/STKB372_CHAT_GPT_ATLAS_B.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.666666666667%2C0%2C66.666666666667%2C100&w=2400)![The ChatGPT browser is already dead](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/10/STKB372_CHAT_GPT_ATLAS_B.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[The ChatGPT browser is already dead](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963654/openai-chatgpt-atlas-ai-browser-shut-down-sunset)\n\nJay PetersJul 9\n\n![Google will now tell you if an ad was made with AI](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/google-ai-ads-label.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=21.77358490566%2C0%2C56.452830188679%2C100&w=2400)![Google will now tell you if an ad was made with AI](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/google-ai-ads-label.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.6603773584906%2C0%2C84.679245283019%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Google will now tell you if an ad was made with AI](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963628/google-ai-generated-ads-label)\n\nStevie BonifieldJul 9\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963571/is-openai-coming-for-squarespace-next)\n\n![David Imel](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/BC24E188-89AF-4EAA-8F30-F4A1EDD99930.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.804979253112%2C0%2C66.390041493776%2C100&w=96)\n\nDavid ImelJul 9\n\nIs OpenAI coming for Squarespace next?\n\nThe new [ChatGPT hosted sites](https://help.openai.com/en/articles/20001339-creating-and-managing-chatgpt-sites) feature is targeted at presenting decks within your business, but it doesn’t seem like much of a stretch for it to become a full-on site builder next.\n\n[![From the ChatGPT Work livestream](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/ChatGPT-Hosted-Sites-Business-Screenshot.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.9035498995311%2C0%2C84.192900200938%2C100&w=2400)](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/ChatGPT-Hosted-Sites-Business-Screenshot.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.9035498995311,0,84.192900200938,100)\n\nFrom the ChatGPT Work livestream\n\nLink\n\n[](/tech/963510/meta-reportedly-plans-to-start-manufacturing-its-new-ai-chip-in-september)\n\n![Emma Roth](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/author_profile_images/195810/EMMA_ROTH.0.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nEmma RothJul 9\n\nMeta reportedly plans to start manufacturing its new AI chip in September.\n\nThe chip, codenamed “Iris,” will join the growing lineup of Meta Training and Inference Accelerators (MTIA), according to a report from *Reuters*. Meta previously announced plans to ship a new in-house chip [every six months](https://about.fb.com/news/2026/03/expanding-metas-custom-silicon-to-power-our-ai-workloads/), helping to decrease its reliance on Nvidia and AMD.\n\n[Meta to put AI chip into production in September](https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/meta-put-ai-chip-into-production-september-it-looks-double-computing-capacity-2026-07-09/)\n\n\\[Reuters\\]\n\nLink\n\n![OpenAI rolls out GPT-5.6 after government greenlight — and announces ‘ChatGPT Work’](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/02/STK155_OPEN_AI_4_CVirginia_A.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.658823529412%2C0%2C66.682352941176%2C100&w=2400)![OpenAI rolls out GPT-5.6 after government greenlight — and announces ‘ChatGPT Work’](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/02/STK155_OPEN_AI_4_CVirginia_A.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0.011761938367442%2C100%2C99.976476123265&w=2400)\n\n[OpenAI rolls out GPT-5.6 after government greenlight — and announces ‘ChatGPT Work’](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963464/openai-gpt-5-6-codex-chatgpt-work)\n\nHayden FieldJul 9\n\n![Microsoft’s patch Tuesdays are about to get bigger](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24038601/acastro_STK109_microsoft_02.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.666666666667%2C0%2C66.666666666667%2C100&w=2400)![Microsoft’s patch Tuesdays are about to get bigger](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24038601/acastro_STK109_microsoft_02.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Microsoft’s patch Tuesdays are about to get bigger](/tech/963307/microsoft-patch-tuesday-ai-security-updates)\n\nStevie BonifieldJul 9\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963452/in-a-court-filing-the-new-york-times-and-other-publications-have-accused-openai-of-withholding-evidence)\n\n![Jay Peters](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/JAY_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nJay PetersJul 9\n\nIn a court filing, The New York Times and other publications have accused OpenAI of withholding evidence.\n\nThe publishers want legal sanctions for OpenAI, and they claim it hasn’t shared information about how “the company’s A.I. systems are trained and used,” [according to *The New York Times*](https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/new-york-times-openai.html).\n\nHere’s [the filing](https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/28443941-memorandum-of-law-in-support-of-news-plaintiffs-motion-for-sanctions-against-openai/), if you want to read it yourself.\n\n*Update: Added a link to the filing.*\n\n[New York Times and Other Publishers Ask Court to Penalize OpenAI](https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/new-york-times-openai.html)\n\n\\[The New York Times\\]\n\nLink\n\n![Meta says its new AI model is ready to compete on coding](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/STK043_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_2_Meta.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=16.666666666667%2C0%2C66.666666666667%2C100&w=2400)![Meta says its new AI model is ready to compete on coding](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/STK043_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_2_Meta.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Meta says its new AI model is ready to compete on coding](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963193/meta-muse-spark-model-api)\n\nDominic Preston and Hayden FieldJul 9\n\n![Say hello to Claude Wrapped](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/Claude-Reflect-graph-blog.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.8125%2C0%2C84.375%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Say hello to Claude Wrapped](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963105/anthropic-claude-wrapped-reflection-ai-usage)\n\nOr, as Anthropic calls it, a ‘reflection dashboard.’\n\nHayden FieldJul 9\n\n![Character.AI wants a piece of the microdrama pie](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/c.ai-Series-1.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=21.875%2C0%2C56.25%2C100&w=2400)![Character.AI wants a piece of the microdrama pie](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/c.ai-Series-1.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.8125%2C0%2C84.375%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[Character.AI wants a piece of the microdrama pie](/entertainment/962897/character-ai-series-microdrama-vertical-video)\n\nCharles Pulliam-MooreJul 9\n\n![FL Studio 2026 turns its AI chatbot into your assistant engineer](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/Hands-on-assistance-built-in.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=21.875%2C0%2C56.25%2C100&w=2400)![FL Studio 2026 turns its AI chatbot into your assistant engineer](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/Hands-on-assistance-built-in.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.8125%2C0%2C84.375%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[FL Studio 2026 turns its AI chatbot into your assistant engineer](/tech/963052/fl-studio-2026-music-daw-ai-chatbot)\n\nTerrence O'BrienJul 9\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963191/chasing-that-2008-high)\n\n![Dominic Preston](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/DOM_BLURPLE-1.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nDominic PrestonJul 9\n\nChasing that 2008 high.\n\nAs San Francisco sellers start [trading houses for AI stock](/tech/962803/stock-for-san-francisco-square-footage#comments), you might wonder whether someone out there is *trying* to run the housing crisis all over again.\n\n**tomatocactus:**\n\n> “How can we make this bubble MORE like the housing crisis” is not a question I expected people to ask\n\nGet the day’s best comment and more in my free newsletter, [*The Verge Daily*](/newsletters).\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/963182/our-biggest-update-for-work-in-chatgpt)\n\n![Thomas Ricker](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/thomas-headshot-purple.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nThomas RickerJul 9\n\n“Our biggest update for work in ChatGPT.”\n\nOpenAI is hosting another [livestream](https://openai.com/live/) on Thursday at 1pm ET, where it’s teasing the following:\n\n> Join us to see how ChatGPT is evolving to help teams take on their most ambitious work—from bringing together context across your business to planning and completing multi-step work, creating polished deliverables, and keeping work moving across desktop, web, and mobile.\n\nLink\n\n[](/business/963069/pc-shipments-fell-for-the-first-time-in-over-two-years-thanks-to-ramageddon)\n\n![Terrence O'Brien](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/TERRENCE_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nTerrence O'BrienJul 8\n\nPC shipments fell for the first time in over two years thanks to RAMageddon.\n\nAfter nine straight quarters of growth, worldwide PC shipments dropped by 4.9 percent year-over-year, according to [IDC](https://www.idc.com/resource-center/press-releases/2q26-pc-top5/). The research firm places the blame for the decline squarely on the [memory chip shortage](/news/839353/pc-ram-shortage-pricing-spike-news) driven by the AI arms race.\n\n[![IDC chart showing worldwide PC shipments over time, with a decline in the last quarter.](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/image.webp?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/image.webp?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0,0,100,100)\n\nImage: IDC\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962998/you-can-and-should-opt-out-of-letting-people-use-your-instagram-posts-with-metas-ai)\n\n![Terrence O'Brien](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/TERRENCE_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nTerrence O'BrienJul 8\n\nYou can (and should) opt out of letting people use your Instagram posts with Meta’s AI.\n\nGo to your profile in the Instagram app and open the hamburger menu in the top right corner. Scroll down to “sharing and reuse,” then toggle off the sliders for “allow people to create with and reuse your content” for Posts and Reels. Then, below that, also turn off “allow people to create and reuse your original audio on [Meta AI](/tech/962485/meta-muse-image-ai-model-instagram).”\n\n[![Options to let people reuse / create with your content using Meta AI.](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/Screenshot_20260708-145327.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=2400)](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/Screenshot_20260708-145327.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0,0,100,100)\n\nScreenshot: Terrence O’Brien / The Verge\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962990/this-week-in-the-big-ai-data-center-buildout)\n\n![Jay Peters](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/JAY_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nJay PetersJul 8\n\nThis week in the big AI data center buildout.\n\nAI data center projects are continuing to pop up across the US, with frequent opposition from locals concerned about their impact. Here are a few recent articles about the projects:\n\n-   *E&E News*: [The data center boom — and its tax promises — run into rural resistance in North Carolina](https://www.eenews.net/articles/the-data-center-boom-and-its-tax-promises-run-into-rural-resistance-in-north-carolina/)\n-   *Fox 5 Atlanta*: [Douglas County data center sparks resident pushback](https://www.fox5atlanta.com/news/douglas-county-data-center-sparks-resident-pushback)\n-   *Missouri Independent*: [Data center backlash spills into Missouri primaries as GOP candidates demand action](https://missouriindependent.com/2026/07/02/data-center-backlash-spills-into-missouri-primaries-as-gop-candidates-demand-action/)\n-   *The San Francisco Chronicle*: [Calistoga won’t pursue data center at fairgrounds after resident backlash](https://www.sfchronicle.com/california/article/calistoga-data-center-22328978.php)\n\nLink\n\n![ChatGPT’s upgraded voice mode is better at shutting up](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/chatgpt-voice-upgrade.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=21.875%2C0%2C56.25%2C100&w=2400)![ChatGPT’s upgraded voice mode is better at shutting up](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/chatgpt-voice-upgrade.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.8125%2C0%2C84.375%2C100&w=2400)\n\n[ChatGPT’s upgraded voice mode is better at shutting up](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962856/chatgpt-upgraded-voice-mode-gpt-live)\n\nEmma RothJul 8\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962752/google-photos-now-lets-you-remix-your-videos-with-ai)\n\n![Stevie Bonifield](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/10/STEVIE_BONIFIELD_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nStevie BonifieldJul 8\n\nGoogle Photos now lets you “remix” your videos with AI.\n\nGoogle’s Video Remix feature, running on [Gemini Omni](/tech/933552/google-gemini-ai-omni-flash-media-video-io-2026), adds new editing options like “cinematic relighting,” custom backgrounds, and “artistic treatments” such as watercolor and sketchbook effects. The AI video editing templates are rolling out starting today for Google AI Plus, Pro, and Ultra subscribers.\n\n[![A gif showing clips of Google’s AI Video Remix feature](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/google-photos-video-remix-gif-optimized.gif?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.6953125%2C0%2C84.609375%2C100&w=2400)](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2026/07/google-photos-video-remix-gif-optimized.gif?quality=90&strip=all&crop=7.6953125,0,84.609375,100)\n\nImage: Google\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962871/amazon-is-reportedly-trying-to-catch-up-in-the-ai-agent-race-with-moonraker)\n\n![Hayden Field](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/06/HAYDEN_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nHayden FieldJul 8\n\nAmazon is reportedly trying to catch up in the AI agent race with “Moonraker.”\n\n*Business Insider* [reported](https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-moonraker-project-alexa-agentic-cost-2026-7) that the project is focused on improving Alexa AI enough to handle more advanced, multi-step tasks, like Google, OpenAI and other AI leaders [have been](/ai-artificial-intelligence/934478/if-google-cant-make-ai-agents-useful-maybe-no-one-can), but internal documents show its steep cost.\n\n[Amazon documents reveal a costly new Alexa AI project](https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-moonraker-project-alexa-agentic-cost-2026-7)\n\n\\[Business Insider\\]\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962840/openai-is-hosting-a-livestream-about-the-all-new-chatgpt-voice-later-today)\n\n![Stevie Bonifield](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/10/STEVIE_BONIFIELD_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nStevie BonifieldJul 8\n\nOpenAI is hosting a livestream about the “all-new ChatGPT Voice” later today.\n\nIt kicks off [at 1PM ET](https://x.com/OpenAI/status/2074871151302774869?s=20). We’ll have to see if the new voice mode works [better than the old one](https://www.tiktok.com/@huskistaken/video/7659517765803314462).\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962675/gpt-5-6-is-go)\n\n![Thomas Ricker](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/thomas-headshot-purple.png?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nThomas RickerJul 8\n\nGPT-5.6 is go.\n\nThe Trump administration has given OpenAI’s [GPT 5.6 model suite](/ai-artificial-intelligence/957845/openai-gpt-5-6-trump-administration-ai-preview) announced on June 26th the green light for public launch, [according to Axios](https://www.axios.com/2026/07/08/openai-gpt-trump-ban-lifted). Sol is the flagship, Terra a medium-tier model for “high-volume work,” and Luna is the “fast and affordable” everyday model.\n\nLink\n\n[](/ai-artificial-intelligence/962540/openais-chief-futurist-is-leaving-the-company-after-nine-years)\n\n![Hayden Field](https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/06/HAYDEN_BLURPLE.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100&w=96)\n\nHayden FieldJul 7\n\nOpenAI’s chief futurist is leaving the company after nine years.\n\nJoshua Achiam, who recently testified in the *Musk v. Altman* trial, [wrote](https://x.com/jachiam0/status/2074605703281693175?s=20) on X that there was “not a specific reason for me leaving, or a specific reason for why now. But it’s something I have been thinking of for a while … it feels possible to work on the mission from outside the walls of a frontier lab.” He added, “The future of humanity depends on the choices we make together about AGI and superintelligence.”\n\n[Joshua Achiam (@jachiam0) on X](https://x.com/jachiam0/status/2074605703281693175?s=20)\n\n\\[X (formerly Twitter)\\]\n\nLink\n\n![Meta’s new Muse Image model can 